This program will convert the IP address given in dotted decimal notation to binary format.

HOW TO COMPILE & BUILD THE EXECUTABLE:
--------------------------------------
1) Checkout the "IP_Dot_Decimal_To_Binary" directory and do not change the directory structure or name inside th
is directory.
2) Go inside "make" directory and give make. This will generate object file into "IP_Dot_Decimal_To_Binary/obj"
directory and executable will be generated inside "IP_Dot_Decimal_To_Binary/bin" directory.
3) Executable name is "ip_addr_to_bin".
4) Give executable permission to the "ip_addr_to_bin" file generated in "IP_Dot_Decimal_To_Binary/bin". (chmod +
x ip_addr_to_bin)
5) If you want to remove the object files and executables, then go inside "IP_Dot_Decimal_To_Binary/make" and gi
ve "make clean". Now, give "make" to compile and generate the executable again.


HOW TO RUN:
----------
1) Go inside "IP_Dot_Decimal_To_Binary/bin".
2) ./ip_addr_to_bin
3) Enter the ip address in dotted decimal form after you get the prompt message
"Enter the IP Address in dotted decimal notation:"

SAMPLE OUTPUTS:
--------------
./ip_addr_to_bin
Enter the IP Address in dotted decimal notation:
1.2.5.44
The binary output for the given IP is:00000001000000100000010100101100


./ip_addr_to_bin
Enter the IP Address in dotted decimal notation:
0.0.0.0
The binary output for the given IP is:00000000000000000000000000000000


./ip_addr_to_bin
Enter the IP Address in dotted decimal notation:
255.255.255.A
Invalid IP
